rthage. This Phoenician name may ultimately be of Semitic origin, and thus related to the biblical <i>Anne</i>. However, the connection, if it exists, is indirect rather than direct."],"variants":[{"name":"Anne","meanings":["variant of   Anne  , in common use as a given name in most European languages. Among people with a classical education, it has from time to time been associated with  Virgil's  Aeneid, where it is borne by the sister of  Dido , Queen of Carthage. This Phoenician name may ultimately be of Semitic origin, and thus related to the biblical <i>Anne</i>. However, the connection, if it exists, is indirect rather than direct."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Anna Poyser was born in 1542, in Brasted, Kent, England, United Kingdom, her father, Nicholas Posyer, was 12 and her mother, Anne Miller, was 11. She had at least 1 son with Robert Heath."},"et":{"1542–":"1542–Surnud","1542–Female":"1542–Surnud","1538–1604":"1538–1604","1574–1644":"1574–1644","1530–1575":"1530–1575","1531–1575":"1531–1575","1644":"1644","1542":"1542","1531":"1531","1575":"1575","1530":"1530","1574":"1574","13 April 1574":"13. aprill 1574","1604":"1604","1538":"1538","Brasted, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Brasted, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England":"Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England"},"fi":{"1542–":"1542–Kuollut","1542–Female":"1542–Kuollut","1538–1604":"1538–1604","1574–1644":"1574–1644","1530–1575":"1530–1575","1531–1575":"1531–1575","1644":"1644","1542":"1542","1531":"1531","1575":"1575","1530":"1530","1574":"1574","13 April 1574":"13. huhtikuuta 1574","1604":"1604","1538":"1538","Brasted, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Brasted, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England":"Salisbury St Martin, Wiltshire, England"},"fr":{"1542–":"1542–Décédée","1542–Female":"1542–Décédée","1538–1604":"1538–1604","1574–1644":"1574–1644","1530–1575":"1530–1575","1531–1575":"1531–1575","1644":"1644","1542":"1542","1531"